#. <section class="sutta" id="sn10.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga"
msgstr "1. With Indaka"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn10.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Paṭhamasukkāsutta"
msgstr "9. With the Nun Sukkā (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.9:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn10.9:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sukkā bhikkhunī mahatiyā parisāya parivutā dhammaṃ "
"deseti."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time the nun Sukkā was teaching Dhamma, surrounded by a large "
"assembly."

msgctxt "sn10.9:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sukkāya bhikkhuniyā abhippasanno yakkho rājagahe rathikāya rathikaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then a native spirit was so devoted to Sukkā that he went street to street "
"and square to square, and on that occasion recited these verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.459"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc842"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.9:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ me katā rājagahe manussā,"
msgstr "“What’s up with these people in Rājagaha?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.9:2.2"
msgid "Madhupītāva seyare;"
msgstr "They sleep like they’ve been drinking mead!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.9:2.3"
msgid "Ye sukkaṃ na payirupāsanti,"
msgstr "They don’t attend on Sukkā"

# In most cases, I have translated the slightly different texts here and at Thig 3.6 the same, this line must clearly be different.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.9:2.4"
msgid "Desentiṃ amataṃ padaṃ."
msgstr "as she’s teaching the deathless state."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc843"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.9:3.1"
msgid "Tañca pana appaṭivānīyaṃ,"
msgstr "But the wise—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.9:3.2"
msgid "Asecanakamojavaṃ;"
msgstr "it’s as if they drink it up,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.9:3.3"
msgid "Pivanti maññe sappaññā,"
msgstr "so irresistible, delicious, and nutritious,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Valāhakamiva panthagū”ti → valāhakamivaddhagūti (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn10.9:3.4"
msgid "Valāhakamiva panthagū”ti."
msgstr "like travelers enjoying a cool cloud.”"
